        <m>{\large \textbf{23.2 The Spectral Theorem}}</m>
        <p>The Spectral Theorem:</p>
        <p>An <m>n \times n</m> symmetric matrix <m>A</m> has the following properties.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    All eigenvalues of <m>A</m> are real.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The eigenspaces are mutually orthogonal.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>A</m> can be diagonalized as <m>A = PDP^T</m>, where <m>D</m> is diagonal and <m>P</m> is orthogonal.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <m></m><p></p><m></m><p></p>
